full_text: U.S. Department of Justice OMB #1115-0052 Immigration and Naturalization Service Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony Naturalization and Citizenship Branch File or A # 300 NORTH LOS ANGELES STREET A 43 088 228 ANGELES CA 90012 Date 0/25/1998 You are hereby notified to appear for a Naturalization Oath Ceremony at the DATE, TIME AND PLACE SHOWN BELOW. Date CHING LEE FONG Time 8:00 AM 612 1/2 NEW HIGH ST #23 LOS ANGELES CA 90012 Place LOS ANGELES CONVENTION CENTER 1201 SOUTH FIGUERDA STREET LOS ANGELES CA 90012 You must bring the following with you: This letter, with ALL of the QUESTIONS ON THE REVERSE side answered in ink or on a typewriter Alien Registration Card. Reentry Permit or Refugee Travel Document. Any immigration documents you may have. If the naturalization application is ON BEHALF OF YOUR CHILD (children), BRING your CHILD (children). If you cannot come to this ceremony, return this notice immediately and state why you cannot appear. In such case, please use th address in the extreme upper left hand corner of this letter. You will be sent another notice of ceremony at a later date. You must a an oath ceremony to complete the naturalization process.
